The currents <italic>I</italic><sub><italic>ion</italic></sub> (for <italic>ion</italic> &#x02208; {<italic>K</italic>, <italic>Na</italic>, <italic>Cl</italic>}) are all of the form
<disp-formula id="pone.0147060.e011"><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="pone.0147060.e011.jpg" id="pone.0147060.e011g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait"/><mml:math id="M11"><mml:mtable displaystyle="true"><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="right"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>I</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">ion</mml:mtext></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">ion</mml:mtext></mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mi>V</mml:mi><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>E</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">ion</mml:mtext></mml:msub><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mspace width="4pt"/><mml:mo>.</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:math></alternatives><label>(11)</label></disp-formula>
Cl<sup>&#x02212;</sup> has a pure leak conductance <inline-formula id="pone.0147060.e012"><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="pone.0147060.e012.jpg" id="pone.0147060.e012g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait"/><mml:math id="M12"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">Cl</mml:mtext></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">Cl</mml:mtext><mml:mi>l</mml:mi></mml:msubsup></mml:mrow></mml:math></alternatives></inline-formula>. The two gating&#x02013;dependent conductances
<disp-formula id="pone.0147060.e013"><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="pone.0147060.e013.jpg" id="pone.0147060.e013g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait"/><mml:math id="M13"><mml:mtable displaystyle="true"><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="right"><mml:msub><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mi>K</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mtd><mml:mtd><mml:mrow><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mi>K</mml:mi><mml:mi>l</mml:mi></mml:msubsup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mi>K</mml:mi><mml:mi>g</mml:mi></mml:msubsup><mml:msup><mml:mi>n</mml:mi><mml:mn>4</mml:mn></mml:msup><mml:mspace width="4pt"/><mml:mo>,</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:math></alternatives><label>(12)</label></disp-formula>
<disp-formula id="pone.0147060.e014"><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="pone.0147060.e014.jpg" id="pone.0147060.e014g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait"/><mml:math id="M14"><mml:mtable displaystyle="true"><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="right"><mml:msub><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">Na</mml:mtext></mml:msub></mml:mtd><mml:mtd><mml:mrow><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">Na</mml:mtext><mml:mi>l</mml:mi></mml:msubsup><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">Na</mml:mtext><mml:mi>g</mml:mi></mml:msubsup><mml:msup><mml:mi>m</mml:mi><mml:mn>3</mml:mn></mml:msup><mml:mi>h</mml:mi><mml:mspace width="4pt"/><mml:mo>,</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:math></alternatives><label>(13)</label></disp-formula>
are the sum of a leak conductance <inline-formula id="pone.0147060.e015"><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="pone.0147060.e015.jpg" id="pone.0147060.e015g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait"/><mml:math id="M15"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">ion</mml:mtext><mml:mi>l</mml:mi></mml:msubsup></mml:math></alternatives></inline-formula> and a gated term with a much higher maximal conductance <inline-formula id="pone.0147060.e016"><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="pone.0147060.e016.jpg" id="pone.0147060.e016g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait"/><mml:math id="M16"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>g</mml:mi><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">ion</mml:mtext><mml:mi>g</mml:mi></mml:msubsup></mml:math></alternatives></inline-formula>. The Nernst potentials <italic>E</italic><sub><italic>ion</italic></sub> depend on the ion concentrations <italic>ion</italic><sub><italic>i</italic>/<italic>e</italic></sub> (for <italic>ion</italic><sub><italic>i</italic>/<italic>e</italic></sub> &#x02208; {<italic>Na</italic><sub><italic>i</italic>/<italic>e</italic></sub>, <italic>K</italic><sub><italic>i</italic>/<italic>e</italic></sub>, <italic>Cl</italic><sub><italic>i</italic>/<italic>e</italic></sub>}) in the intra&#x02013;/extracellular space ICS/ECS, and on the ion valence <italic>z</italic><sub><italic>ion</italic></sub>:
<disp-formula id="pone.0147060.e017"><alternatives><graphic xlink:href="pone.0147060.e017.jpg" id="pone.0147060.e017g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait"/><mml:math id="M17"><mml:mtable displaystyle="true"><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="right"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>E</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mi>o</mml:mi><mml:mi>n</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:mn>26</mml:mn><mml:mo>.</mml:mo><mml:mn>64</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>z</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mi>o</mml:mi><mml:mi>n</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mfrac><mml:mo form="prefix">ln</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">ion</mml:mtext><mml:mi>e</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>/</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">ion</mml:mtext><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:math></alternatives><label>(14)</label></disp-formula>
The coefficient 26.64 mV is computed from the ideal gas constant, the absolute temperature, and Faraday&#x02019;s constant. All parameters are listed in <xref rid="pone.0147060.t001" ref-type="table">Table 1</xref>. They are commonly used for this type of simplified single unit description [<xref rid="pone.0147060.ref042" ref-type="bibr">42</xref>, <xref rid="pone.0147060.ref043" ref-type="bibr">43</xref>, <xref rid="pone.0147060.ref050" ref-type="bibr">50</xref>&#x02013;<xref rid="pone.0147060.ref052" ref-type="bibr">52</xref>], and the conductances and gating dynamics are based on an experimental estimation by Gutkin et al. [<xref rid="pone.0147060.ref054" ref-type="bibr">54</xref>].</p><table-wrap id="pone.0147060.t001" orientation="portrait" position="float"><object-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1371/journal.pone.0147060.t001</object-id><label>Table 1</label><caption><title>Model parameters.</title></caption><alternatives><graphic id="pone.0147060.t001g" xlink:href="pone.0147060.t001"/><table frame="box" rules="all" border="0"><colgroup span="1"><col align="left" valign="middle" span="1"/><col align="left" valign="middle" span="1"/><col align="left" valign="middle" span="1"/></colgroup><thead><tr><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Name</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Value &#x00026; unit</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><italic>C</italic><sub><italic>m</italic></sub></td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">1 <italic>&#x003bc;</italic>F/cm<sup>2</sup></td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">membrane capacitance</td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><italic>&#x003d5;</italic></td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">3/msec</td><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">gating time scale parameter</td></tr><tr><td align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">
